      "character": "breath_master",
      "text": "Notice—every inhale asks 'What?' and every exhale answers 'am I?' You've been breathing the question your whole life without knowing. The question isn't thought—it's as natural as breath itself.",
      "subtext": "questioning as respiration",
      "emotional_state": "breathing wisdom",
      "visual_cue": "breath visible as question marks in cold air"
    },
    {
      "character": "evan",
      "text": "So I don't need to think the question—I need to breathe it?",
      "subtext": "embodied inquiry",
      "emotional_state": "respiratory recognition",
      "visual_cue": "breathing becoming conscious and visible"
    },
    {
      "character": "breath_master",
      "text": "The question breathes you. 'What am I?' isn't something you do but something that does you. Like breath—automatic yet conscious, necessary yet free.",
      "subtext": "passive activity paradox",
      "emotional_state": "effortless effort",
      "visual_cue": "being breathed by existence"
    },
    {
      "character": "evan",
      "text": "I feel it—the universe breathing curiosity through me!",
      "subtext": "cosmic respiration",
      "emotional_state": "pneumatic joy",
      "visual_cue": "expanding with each breath-question"
    },
    {
      "character": "breath_master",
      "text": "Now you understand—'What am I?' is the universe breathing itself awake through you. Every breath a question, every question a breath, consciousness respirating into being.",
